# Product Requirements Document (PRD)
# AI Code Review Agent

**Version:** 1.0.0
**Author:** Jai Obulisamy
**Status:** Draft
**Last Updated:** 2026-03-10

---

## 1. Project Overview

### 1.1 Summary
An AI-powered code review agent that automatically analyzes code for bugs, security vulnerabilities, style issues, performance problems, and test coverage gaps. The agent integrates with GitHub to post inline PR comments and also provides a browser-based Web UI for on-demand reviews. It is powered by the Claude API (Anthropic) and maintains per-repo review history to deliver increasingly context-aware feedback over time.

### 1.2 Elevator Pitch
> "An AI agent that reviews your pull requests like a senior engineer — catching bugs, flagging security holes, and suggesting improvements — all posted directly as GitHub PR comments."

### 1.3 Resume Value
This project demonstrates:
- Full-stack development (React frontend + Python/FastAPI backend)
- AI/LLM integration (Claude API with structured prompting)
- GitHub OAuth & REST API integration
- Persistent data layer (per-repo review history)
- Agentic system design (multi-step analysis pipeline)
- Local Docker-based development environment

---

## 2. Goals & Success Criteria

| Goal | Success Metric |
|------|---------------|
| Analyze a PR in under 30 seconds | ≤ 30s end-to-end review time |
| Cover all 5 feedback categories | All categories present in every review |
| Post comments directly to GitHub PRs | GitHub API integration working |
| Web UI is functional and clean | User can paste code and get a review |
| Per-repo history improves context | History stored and injected into prompts |

