## 6. Core Features

### 6.1 Feature 1 — Web UI Code Review
**Description:** User pastes code into a browser interface, selects a language, and receives an AI-generated review.

**Requirements:**
- Code editor input (syntax-highlighted textarea or Monaco editor)
- Language selector dropdown (Python, JavaScript, TypeScript, Java, Go, etc.)
- "Review Code" button triggers backend API call
- Results displayed as categorized, inline-annotated feedback
- Each finding shows: severity (error/warning/info), line number, category, and suggestion

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] User can paste code and receive a review in < 30 seconds
- [ ] Output is organized by category (Bug, Security, Style, Performance, Tests)
- [ ] Each finding links to the relevant line number

---

### 6.2 Feature 2 — GitHub PR Integration
**Description:** When a PR is opened or updated, the agent automatically reviews the diff and posts inline comments on GitHub.

**Requirements:**
- GitHub App or OAuth App configured with webhook on `pull_request` events
- Backend receives webhook, extracts PR diff via GitHub API
- Diff is sent through review pipeline
- Findings posted as inline review comments on the specific lines
- Summary comment posted at top of PR with overall score and category breakdown

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Webhook received and processed within 10 seconds of PR creation
- [ ] Inline comments appear on correct lines in GitHub UI
- [ ] Summary comment includes: total issues found, breakdown by category, severity counts

---

### 6.3 Feature 3 — Review Analysis Pipeline
**Description:** The multi-step agent pipeline that processes code and produces structured feedback.

**Pipeline Steps:**
1. **Chunker** — Split large files into reviewable chunks (max ~300 lines per chunk)
2. **History Loader** — Query SQLite for past reviews on same repo; inject as context
3. **Claude API Call** — Send structured prompt with code, history context, and instructions
4. **Response Parser** — Parse Claude's JSON-structured output into finding objects
5. **Comment Poster** — Map findings to GitHub inline comments or Web UI response

**Prompt Design:**
```
System: You are an expert code reviewer. Analyze the following code and return 
a JSON array of findings. Each finding must include:
- category: "bug" | "security" | "style" | "performance" | "test_coverage"
- severity: "error" | "warning" | "info"
- line_start: integer
- line_end: integer
- title: string (short)
- description: string (detailed explanation)
- suggestion: string (concrete fix)

Previous review context for this repo: {history_context}
Language: {language}
Code:
{code_chunk}
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Pipeline handles files up to 1,000 lines
- [ ] Structured JSON always returned and parseable
- [ ] History context injected when available

---

### 6.4 Feature 4 — Per-Repo Review History
**Description:** Store all past reviews per repository to give the agent growing context over time.

**Data Model:**
```sql
-- repos table
CREATE TABLE repos (
  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
  github_repo_id TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,
  repo_name TEXT NOT NULL,
  created_at DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

-- reviews table
CREATE TABLE reviews (
  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
  repo_id INTEGER REFERENCES repos(id),
  pr_number INTEGER,
  file_path TEXT,
  code_snippet TEXT,
  findings_json TEXT,  -- JSON array of findings
  reviewed_at DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Every review is saved to SQLite after completion
- [ ] On next review of same repo, last 5 reviews are loaded as context
- [ ] History is summarized (not raw) before injection to save tokens

---

### 6.5 Feature 5 — Review Dashboard (Web UI)
**Description:** A simple dashboard showing review history, stats, and past findings.

**Requirements:**
- List of past reviews with date, repo name, file, and finding counts
- Click into any past review to see full findings
- Simple stats bar: total reviews run, total bugs found, total security issues

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Dashboard loads past reviews from backend API
- [ ] Stats update after each new review
- [ ] Responsive layout (desktop + tablet)

---

## 7. API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| POST | `/api/review` | Submit code for Web UI review |
| POST | `/api/webhook/github` | Receive GitHub PR webhook |
| GET | `/api/reviews` | List all past reviews |
| GET | `/api/reviews/{id}` | Get a single review's findings |
| GET | `/api/repos` | List all tracked repos |
| GET | `/api/health` | Health check |

