## 10. Development Phases

### Phase 1 — Foundation (Week 1-2)
- [ ] Set up repo, Docker Compose, and project structure
- [ ] Build FastAPI backend skeleton with health check
- [ ] Set up SQLite with SQLAlchemy models
- [ ] Integrate Anthropic SDK — basic Claude call working

### Phase 2 — Core Agent (Week 2-3)
- [ ] Build review pipeline (chunker → prompt → parse)
- [ ] Implement `/api/review` endpoint
- [ ] Write prompt templates for all 5 feedback categories
- [ ] Validate structured JSON output from Claude

### Phase 3 — Web UI (Week 3-4)
- [ ] Scaffold React + Vite + Tailwind frontend
- [ ] Build CodeEditor component
- [ ] Build ReviewResults + FindingCard components
- [ ] Connect frontend to backend API

### Phase 4 — GitHub Integration (Week 4-5)
- [ ] Create GitHub App, configure webhooks
- [ ] Implement webhook receiver endpoint
- [ ] Post inline PR comments via GitHub API
- [ ] Post summary comment on PR

### Phase 5 — History & Dashboard (Week 5-6)
- [ ] Save all reviews to SQLite
- [ ] Build history context injection into pipeline
- [ ] Build Dashboard page with past reviews & stats

### Phase 6 — Polish (Week 6)
- [ ] Error handling, loading states, edge cases
- [ ] README with screenshots and setup guide
- [ ] Demo video / GIF for resume/portfolio

---

## 11. Out of Scope (v1.0)

- Cloud deployment (intentionally local-only for v1)
- User authentication / multi-user support
- Support for compiled languages (C++, Rust) beyond basic analysis
- Automatic code fix suggestions (auto-PR creation)
- Slack / email notifications

---

## 12. Risks & Mitigations

| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|------------|
| Claude API costs exceed budget | Medium | Set max_tokens limits, cache repeat reviews |
| GitHub webhook setup complexity | Medium | Use ngrok for local webhook tunneling |
| Large PRs exceed context window | Medium | Chunker splits files into ≤300 line segments |
| JSON parsing failures from Claude | Low | Add retry logic + fallback plain-text parser |

---

## 13. Stretch Goals (v2.0)

- [ ] Deploy to Vercel (frontend) + Railway (backend)
- [ ] Support multi-model comparison (Claude vs GPT-4)
- [ ] VS Code extension integration
- [ ] Severity score trend chart per repo over time
- [ ] Auto-suggest fixes via Claude (not just identify issues)

